{% extends "layout.html.twig" %}

{% block content %}
    <h1>Download Octower</h1>

    <p>Run this in your terminal to get the latest Octower version:</p>
    <code>curl -sS https://getoctower.org/installer | php</code>

    <p>Or if you don't have curl:</p>
    <code>php -r "eval('?>'.file_get_contents('https://getoctower.org/installer'));"</code>

    <p>This installer script will simply check some php.ini settings, warn you if they are set incorrectly, and then download the latest octower.phar in the current directory</p>

    <h2>Installer Options</h2>

    <h3>--install-dir</h3>
    <p>You can install octower to a specific directory by using the <code>--install-dir</code> option and providing a target directory. Options must be appended to <code>--</code> so that PHP ignores them, like <code>-- --install-dir=bin</code>, example:</p>
    <code>curl -sS https://getoctower.org/installer | php -- --install-dir=bin</code>

    <h3>--filename</h3>
    <p>You can specify the filename (default: octower.phar) using the <code>--filename</code> option. example:</p>
    <code>curl -sS https://getoctower.org/installer | php -- --filename=octower</code>

    <h3>--version</h3>
    <p>You can install octower to a specific release by using the <code>--version</code> option and providing a target release. example:</p>
    <code>curl -sS https://getoctower.org/installer | php -- --version=1.0.0</code>

    {#
        <h2>Windows Installer</h2>
        <p>The installer will download octower for you and set up your PATH environment variable so you can simply call <code>octower</code> from any directory.</p>
        <p>Download and run <a href="/Octower-Setup.exe">Octower-Setup.exe</a> - it will install the latest octower version whenever it is executed.</p>
    #}

    <h2>Manual Download</h2>
    <p>If you prefer to download the phar manually, here are the available versions:</p>
    <p>
        <a href="{{ app.request.basePath }}/octower.phar">Latest Snapshot</a> ({{ latestSnapshotDate|date('Y-m-d') }})<br />
        {% for version, date in versions %}
            <a href="{{ path('download_version', {version: version}) }}">{{ version }}</a> ({{ date|date('Y-m-d') }})<br />
        {% endfor %}
    </p>
{% endblock %}
